        <h1>Azure container registry</h1>
        <p>
            its registry where u store all docker images.
        </p>
        A Docker image is a read-only template containing everything needed to run an application, 
        including the code, runtime, system tools, libraries, and settings. 
        It's essentially a snapshot or blueprint of the application's environment. 
   <ul>
    <li>
        <h3> how to create container registry</h3>
        1.create resource group
        2. create container registry (it had premium and standard --if standard store in only one region, premium it will store to mutiple regions)
        3. once created push the docker image to container
    </li>
